claim: Sources of uncertainty were identified systematically in all parts of the assessment, starting from the planning stage (step B in Figure 5 of EFSA Scientific Committee, 2018a).
title: Figure B.1.
caption: Criteria for evaluating if there is a significant dose–response

claim: The analysis was divided into parts on three levels, corresponding to the structure of the hazard assessment, as illustrated in the upper part of Figure 1.
title: Figure 1.
caption: Diagram of the conceptual model for the uncertainty analysis of the hazard assessment for HOCs other than genotoxicity, the uncertainty analysis for which was conducted separately and is described in Section 2.3.4.2. See text for further explanation

claim: For each of the 21 clusters in the other HOCs, uncertainty was quantified by means of two quantitative expert judgements, comprising a third level of division in the uncertainty analysis, as illustrated in Figure 1.
title: Figure 1.
caption: Diagram of the conceptual model for the uncertainty analysis of the hazard assessment for HOCs other than genotoxicity, the uncertainty analysis for which was conducted separately and is described in Section 2.3.4.2. See text for further explanation

claim: The combination was conducted in three steps, as illustrated in the lower part of Figure 1.
title: Figure 1.
caption: Diagram of the conceptual model for the uncertainty analysis of the hazard assessment for HOCs other than genotoxicity, the uncertainty analysis for which was conducted separately and is described in Section 2.3.4.2. See text for further explanation

claim:

The two questions for each cluster (see Figure 1) were assessed by expert judgement.

claim: After a screening for the reliability and relevance of the results, six studies from four publications, all ranked as of limited relevance, were selected for further consideration (Figure 3 and Table 15).
title: Figure D13A.
caption:
Impact of excluding different clusters on the 5th percentile of the overall enveloped cpf (upper panel) and overall averaged cpf (lower panel) for the estimated lowest BMD across clusters
Each bar shows the lower and upper bound for the fifth percentile when the indicated cluster was excluded. The bottom bar (‘all’) shows the result when no clusters were omitted.

claim: The overview of the evaluation and the summary of the test results from the 22 studies are reported in Figure 4.

caption:

claim: The overview of the evaluation and the summary of the test results from the 21 studies are reported in Figure 5 and in Table 16.
title: Figure B.1.
caption: Criteria for evaluating if there is a significant dose–response

claim: The methods used to quantify the combined impact of the uncertainties affecting the hazard characterisation for HOCs other than genotoxicity are described in Section 2.3.4.1, in which an overview of the approach is provided in Figure 1.
title: Figure 1.
caption: Diagram of the conceptual model for the uncertainty analysis of the hazard assessment for HOCs other than genotoxicity, the uncertainty analysis for which was conducted separately and is described in Section 2.3.4.2. See text for further explanation

claim: The cpfs for the 21 clusters were then combined to produce overall cpfs quantifying uncertainty about the estimated lowest BMD across all the 21 clusters, as illustrated diagrammatically in Figure 1 in Section 2.3.4.1.
title: Figure 1.
caption: Diagram of the conceptual model for the uncertainty analysis of the hazard assessment for HOCs other than genotoxicity, the uncertainty analysis for which was conducted separately and is described in Section 2.3.4.2. See text for further explanation

claim: These revised judgements were used to produce revised overall cpfs quantifying uncertainty about the estimated lowest BMD across all 21 clusters, which are shown in Figure 7.
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: The horizontal axis of Figure 7 shows the range of doses in which the estimated lowest BMD across all 21 clusters is considered to lie.
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: Thus Figure 7 can be used to derive probabilities for the estimated lowest BMD across all 21 clusters being either above or below the RP.
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: The black dashed curves in Figure 7 are lower and upper bounds for the overall enveloped cpf, which reflect the combined effect of differences between experts in their judgements on each cluster.
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: The red solid curves in Figure 7 are lower and upper bounds for the overall averaged cpf, for which the cpfs of different experts for the same cluster are combined by averaging, giving equal weight to each expert.
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: The vertical blue dotted line in Figure 7 marks the dose corresponding to the RP (8.2 ng BPA/kg bw per day, expressed as HED) and the horizontal blue dotted lines show four estimates of the cumulative probability for this dose, i.e. the probability that the lowest BMD across all 21 clusters is below the RP.
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: The results in Figure 7 are an estimate of the combined impact of those uncertainties which were considered by the experts when making judgements on each of the 21 clusters included in the preceding steps.
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: The outcome of this analysis is shown by the cumulative probability functions in Figure 7, which quantify uncertainty about the dose at which the lowest BMD across all clusters would lie if all the uncertainties were resolved, assessed by a structured process of expert judgement (EKE).
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: Sensitivity analysis showed that the lowest part of the overall averaged cpf in Figure 7 (up to 5% probability on the vertical axis) was determined mainly by the cluster allergic lung inflammation and, in particular, by the study by O'Brien et al. (2014) [RefID 5462], reporting effects on production of pro‐inflammatory mediators and specific IgE in mice exposed prenatally to BPA.
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: Allergic lung inflammation was also the largest contributor to the middle part of the overall averaged cpf in Figure 7 (around 50% probability on the vertical axis), but here other clusters also contributed significantly (cellular immunity, inflammation and, to a lesser extent, male and female reproductive toxicity; see Figure D.13B in Appendix D).
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: In the final step of the uncertainty analysis the CEP Panel assessed by expert judgement their probability that the lowest estimated BMD is below the RP, taking into account the estimates of this probability in Figure 7 and also additional uncertainties (Appendix D, Table D.5) that were not quantified earlier.
title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

27

title: Figure D.16.
caption: Sensitivity analysis assessing the impact of hypothetical dependencies between allergic lung inflammation and cellular immunity on the overall enveloped cpf (left hand graph) and overall averaged cpf (right hand graph). See text for explanation

claim: Based on the lower and upper bounds for the averaged cpf in Figure 7, the probability of the lowest estimated BMD being below this dose would be between 43% and 57%, bracketing the 50% probability that would apply to a median estimate, as shown by the green solid lines in the figure.
title: Figure D.16.
